HEADWORD: curriculae
<hw>cur*ric"u*lae</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧r*r⟦icr⟧k"⟦umac⟧*l⟦emac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Presumably a pseudo-Latinate coinage based on
<er>curricula</er>. See <er>Curriculum</er>.]</ety> <def>Same as
<er>curricula</er>, plural of <er>curriculum</er>. This is used commonly
in the same sense as <er>curricula</er>, and appears to have arisen due
to an incorrect assumption that <er>curricula</er> is a Latin-derived
singular word.</def> <mark>[Ungrammatical]</mark>⟦br⟧
